## Coding Conventions

### Always use Page Object Model (POM)
- Each major page or feature area gets its own Page Object class in `/tests/pages/`
- Page Objects expose semantic methods, not raw locators
- Example:
```ts
export class LoginPage {
  constructor(private page: Page) {}
  async loginAs(username: string, password: string) { ... }
}
```

### Locator Priority (in order of preference)
1. `data-testid` attributes
2. ARIA roles: `getByRole('button', { name: /submit/i })`
3. Labels: `getByLabel(/email/i)`
4. Text: `getByText(...)` — use sparingly
5. CSS selectors — last resort only

### Environment Variables
Never hardcode credentials or URLs. All in `.env` (gitignored).
```
BASE_URL=https://ohm-stg.preprod.ludev.team
LUMEN_ADMIN_URL=

# Instructor/teacher account (course owner)
OHM_TEACHER_USERNAME=
OHM_TEACHER_PASSWORD=

# Admin account (NOT course owner — simulates support team)
OHM_ADMIN_USERNAME=
OHM_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Student account
OHM_STUDENT_USERNAME=
OHM_STUDENT_PASSWORD=

# Test data
TEST_COURSE_ID=
TEST_ENROLLMENT_KEY=
OHM_TEST_GROUP=Hogwarts
```

### Authentication
- Create `tests/helpers/auth.setup.ts` that saves storage state for each role
- Three auth fixtures needed: `instructor.json`, `admin.json`, `student.json`
- Reference in `playwright.config.ts` as project dependencies
- Use `test.use({ storageState: 'tests/fixtures/auth/instructor.json' })` per describe block

### Risk Levels
Tag tests with `@high`, `@medium`, `@low`:
```ts
test('1.1 — Login @high', ...)
```
Run by risk: `npx playwright test --grep @high`

### Multi-Context Tests (Payment Suite)
Some payment tests require 3 simultaneous browser contexts:
1. Teacher window (OHM — controls group payment settings)
2. Lumen Admin window (Fast Forward / Destroy EnrollmentLog)
3. Student window (OHM — experiences paywall)

Pattern:
```ts
test('payment flow', async ({ browser }) => {
  const teacherCtx = await browser.newContext();
  const studentCtx = await browser.newContext();
  // ... test ...
  await teacherCtx.close();
  await studentCtx.close();
});
```

### New Tab / Popup Handling
```ts
const [newPage] = await Promise.all([
  context.waitForEvent('page'),
  page.getByRole('link', { name: /link text/i }).click(),
]);
await newPage.waitForLoadState();
expect(newPage.url()).toContain('expected-domain.com');
```

