## ⚠️ Critical Business Logic & Gotchas

### Payment Settings (MOST IMPORTANT)
- Payment settings are ALWAYS read from the **course owner's group**, never the logged-in user
- If an admin creates a course using the standard "Add New Course" button, the course is owned by the **admin**, not the teacher — this breaks payment settings (regression from OHM-1141)
- Correct admin flow for creating a course on behalf of a teacher:
  `Admin Page → find teacher by name → click "Add Course" from the gray menu bar`
- When writing payment tests, always assert which account owns the course

### OHM Groups
- OHM group = Waymaker account = Lumen Admin institution
- A user must be assigned to a group for their courses to have payment options
- "Not required" payment setting removes payment from ALL courses in that group
- Group assignment is set via: `Admin Page → Search user → Edit user → Group dropdown`

### Student EnrollmentLog (Payment Tests)
- `enrollment_id` visible in page source: `<!-- enrollmentid / enrollment_id = 117 -->`
- Not present if: course has no payment, OR user is logged in as teacher/admin
- Fast Forward = simulate trial expiry
- Destroy = reset student state to re-run payment scenarios
- Both actions are in Lumen Admin → Enrollment Logs

### Known Bugs / Pending Changes
- **User Settings**: Accessibility/Display Preferences changing in upcoming sprint — skip those tests
- **Admin Groups page**: Missing breadcrumb dashboard — known bug, don't assert for it
- **Blank LTI course secret**: Appears saveable — potential security bug (OHM note)
- **New Instructors Report**: Meaningful only in Production — skip in staging or tag `@production-only`
- **Gradebook status flags**: Require specific seeded student data states (IP, OT, PT, EC, NC, NS, LP etc.)
- **Desmos**: Requires its own dedicated test section — placeholder only for now
- **Debug Mode** (Utilities): Do not automate — use `test.skip()`
- **Update ExtRefs** (Utilities): Marked dangerous in spec — do not automate
- **LMS Integration / Canvas**: Requires Canvas LMS environment — separate suite, tag `@canvas`

### Destructive Tests (Delete, Batch Operations)
- Always create a dedicated temp course/user in `beforeEach` before testing delete flows
- Never delete shared test fixtures
- Clean up in `afterEach` or `afterAll`

